def find_paths_in_bearland(n, k, a, b, c, d):
    if n != 4:
        return -1
    if k < n + 1:
        return -1
    vertices = set(range(1, n + 1))
    vertices.remove(a)
    vertices.remove(b)
    vertices.remove(c)
    vertices.remove(d)
    lst = []
    lst.append(a)
    lst.append(c)
    for x in vertices:
        lst.append(x)
    lst.append(d)
    lst.append(b)
    path1 = lst[:]
    path2 = [lst[1], lst[0]] + lst[2:-2] + [lst[-1], lst[-2]]
    return (path1, path2)
